scenarios.gherkin:
Given valid registration payload {name: 'Test User', email: 'test@example.com', phone: '555-0000'}
When POST /api/register is called
Then response status is 200 OK
And response Content-Type header is 'application/json'
And response body contains: {success: true, message, user}
And user object includes: {id (numeric), name, email, phone, registeredAt}
And user.id is unique and non-zero
And user.registeredAt is formatted timestamp

Given user exists with id=123
When PUT /api/users/123 is called with {name: 'Updated', email: 'updated@example.com', phone: '555-9999'}
Then response status is 200 OK
And response body is {success: true, message: '...', user: {...updated data...}}
When PUT /api/users/123 is called with {name: '', email: 'test@example.com'} (empty name)
Then response status is 400
And response body is {error: 'Name and email are required'}
When PUT /api/users/9999999 is called (non-existent user)
Then response status is 404
And response body is {error: 'User not found'}
